extracts pdf inforation, converts it to text and html and creates a xml database with its data and word count
given the folder BOOKS will create BOOKS_xml folder containing xml files named after the sha256 signature of each pdf file found.
each file will contain the pdf converted to html encoded as base64, information about the pdf file and stemmized word count.
additionally a file called pdfdb_BOOKS.xml will contain the details of each file including full file name, folder, size, sha256 signature, among other metadata.
there's also a pdfdb_BOOKS.nfo showing statistics of the database as number of files, duplicates, total size, etc.
